hnology. These engaging conversations offer a portrait of an influential community that is subverting and redefining the medium of video games by placing queerness front and center.Interviewees:Ryan Rose Aceae, Avery Alder, Jimmy Andrews, Santo Aveiro-Ojeda, Aevee Bee, Tonia B******, Mattie Brice, Nicky Case, Naomi Clark, Mo Cohen, Heather Flowers, Nina Freeman, Jerome Hagen, Kat Jones, Jess Marcotte, Andi McClure, Llaura McGee, Seanna Musgrave, Liz Ryerson, Elizabeth Sampat, Loren Schmidt, Sarah Schoemann, Dietrich Squinkifer, Kara Stone, Emilia Yang, Robert Yang  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aGay culture. 0aGender identity. 0aQueer theory. 0aVideo game designersvInterviews. 0aVideo gamesxSocial aspects. 7aNON-CLASSIFIABLE.2bisacsh1 aAlder, Avery, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndrews, Jimmy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBee, Aevee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrice, Mattie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCase, Nicky, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClark, Naomi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCohen, Mo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreeman, Nina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHagan, Jerome, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Kat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcClure, Andi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGee, Llaura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMusgrave, Seanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyerson, Liz, econtr